<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-6774] BuilderASTTransformation uses wrong class loader to load builder strategy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6774</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BuilderASTTransform loads builder strategies with the source unit&apos;s class loader, rather than the transform loader. As a result, compilation of code using @Builder fails in Gradle (and other tools that make a distinction between these class loaders). Solution is to use the transform loader, as for example done by TraitASTTransformation. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12817530">GROOVY-6774</key>
            <summary>BuilderASTTransformation uses wrong class loader to load builder strategy</summary>
