                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14475918" author="paulk" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 04:12:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should be fixed in master and the 2_3_X branch. If you have a chance to test, that would be great.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475852" author="pschumacher" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 12:08:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As Paul fixed this issue for 2.3.1 I&apos;m resolving it. Please reopen if the error still occurs. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475919" author="paulk" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 19:33:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, I left it open because there is no test case which actually checks the loader being used and it wasn&apos;t easy to create such a test. I guess as long as it is working in gradle, we should be fine for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475934" author="pniederw" created="Wed, 21 May 2014 00:39:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;According to user feedback (&lt;a href=&quot;http://forums.gradle.org/gradle/topics/the_new_builder_annotation_with_externalstrategy_in_groovy_2_3_1_still_result_in_compilation_error_if_build_with_gradle&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://forums.gradle.org/gradle/topics/the_new_builder_annotation_with_externalstrategy_in_groovy_2_3_1_still_result_in_compilation_error_if_build_with_gradle&lt;/a&gt;), `@Builder` now works when the default strategy is used, but stills fails when an explicit strategy is used. I think the problem is that `strategyClass.getTypeClass()` still loads the strategy class with the wrong class loader (needs to be loaded with transform loader).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14475872" author="pniederw" created="Wed, 21 May 2014 00:48:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(What I don&apos;t understand is why this is only a problem when a strategy is explicitly specified. Nevertheless, I&apos;m pretty sure that getting rid of `strategyClass.getTypeClass()` will solve the problem.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14480550" author="paulk" created="Wed, 21 May 2014 04:29:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The isAssignableFrom check is now delayed and done on the class of the instance returned by the transform loader. Hopefully this should work in all scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
